          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The sphere is centered in its local coordinate system. For example, if you create a sphere whose radius is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "5.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", it extends from "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "-5.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "5.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " along each of the the x, y, and z-axes. A radius of zero or less creates an empty geometry."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
